<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Maybe the main way for things to go wrong in f=
inancial markets is the one that goes by the name =E2=80=9Cpicking up penni=
es in front of a steamroller.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#=
footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: no=
ne !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bl=
ock;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The shape of the problem is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You think that tomorrow will look rou=
ghly the same as today.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You make a=
 bet of the form =E2=80=9Ctomorrow will be roughly the same as today.=E2=80=
=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If tomorrow is roughly the sam=
e as today, you make a small amount of money.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">If tomorrow is very different from today, you lose a ton of mon=
ey.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not necessarily a mistake. Perhaps you=
 have good reason to believe tomorrow will be the same as today, or perhaps=
 you are being well compensated for the risk that it won=E2=80=99t be. Sell=
ing insurance is a classic form of this trade, and insurance companies tend=
 to be profitable. Still, pretty much any time there=E2=80=99s a disaster i=
n financial markets, you can describe the disaster by saying =E2=80=9Csome =
people got too complacent that the future would be just like the recent pas=
t, so they made big bets on that outcome, which they thought were low-risk,=
 but=C2=A0those bets turned out to be riskier than they thought.=E2=80=9D=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sometimes, when this happens, the people makin=
g those bets were naive or stupid or reckless. Other times, they were makin=
g reasonable bets that offered them fair expected returns for the risks the=
y were knowingly taking, but things worked out poorly. They usually look ba=
d in hindsight though.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The most schematic form of this is selling sto=
ck options: Buying stock options is a bet on volatility, a bet that stock p=
rices will move around a lot, so=C2=A0<em>selling=C2=A0</em>stock options i=
s a bet=C2=A0<em>against=C2=A0</em>volatility, a bet that everything will s=
tay the same. Options-selling strategies look very good when volatility sta=
ys low: You make steady returns every day by selling options that don=E2=80=
=99t pay off. And then when something changes, you can lose all your money.=
 Again, this tends to look bad in hindsight. We have <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34642576.286368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDctMTcvZnJlZS10cmFkZXMtY2FuLXJlYWx=
seS1jb3N0LXlvdT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzExMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJn=
V0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAzMTEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c=
3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB40316552" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">talked</a> about various=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34642576.286368/a=
